Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update package list and install Python + pytest requirements
    apt-get update -qq
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    ##############  Prepare initial filesystem state  ##############
    # Base directory for the exercise
    mkdir -p /home/user

    # 1. Create /home/user/data/live and a placeholder SQLite file
    mkdir -p /home/user/data/live
    : > /home/user/data/live/important.db   # create empty file

    # 2. Create archives directory and the *broken* symlink
    mkdir -p /home/user/archives
    ln -sf /home/user/data/old_live /home/user/archives/snap_latest

    # 3. Make sure the student (non-root) can modify everything under /home/user
    chmod -R a+rwX /home/user

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author Backup-Integrity Exercise

%help
    This Apptainer image sets up the initial state for the
    “symbolic-link integrity” exercise.
    Pre-installed: Python 3 + pytest.
    Pre-created:
      • /home/user/data/live/important.db
      • /home/user/archives/snap_latest  (broken symlink -> /home/user/data/old_live)
    Students will repair and validate the links as described in the task.